    <item>
      <title>A database of funding for postdocs &amp; ECRs</title>
      <link>https://asntech.github.io/post/database-of-fundings-for-postdocs/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 20 Feb 2018 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://asntech.github.io/post/database-of-fundings-for-postdocs/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://asntech.github.io/postdoc-funding-schemes/postdoc-funding-banner.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In early 2018, I became the &lt;a href=&#34;https://elifesciences.org/inside-elife/912b0679/early-career-advisory-group-elife-welcomes-150-ambassadors-of-good-practice-in-science&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;eLife Ambassador&lt;/a&gt; along with more than 150 others to work to catalyse improvements in the way science is communicated and performed.
I have joined the initiatives, with focus on;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Science communication, publishing, funding, open access, open science, preprints, and reproducibility&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the funding initiative, the eLife Ambassadors created a comprehensive Excel sheet of funding schemes and opportunities for postdocs and early career researchers. I then turned that Excel sheet into a searchable HTML &lt;a href=&#34;https://asntech.github.io/postdoc-funding-schemes/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;page&lt;/a&gt;, which was later taken off on Twitter.
&lt;blockquote class=&#34;twitter-tweet&#34; data-cards=&#34;hidden&#34; data-lang=&#34;en&#34;&gt;&lt;p lang=&#34;en&#34; dir=&#34;ltr&#34;&gt;Very useful for all &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/hashtag/postdocs?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;#postdocs&lt;/a&gt;: List of &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/hashtag/funding?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;#funding&lt;/a&gt; schemes and opportunities for postdoctoral &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/hashtag/fellowships?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;#fellowships&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://t.co/geFXpH6GFn&#34;&gt;https://t.co/geFXpH6GFn&lt;/a&gt; created by &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/hashtag/eLifeAmbassadors?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;#eLifeAmbassadors&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/eLifeCommunity?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;@eLifeCommunity&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;mdash; Lotte de Winde (@lotte_dewinde) &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/lotte_dewinde/status/959178973593985025?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;February 1, 2018&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote class=&#34;twitter-tweet&#34; data-cards=&#34;hidden&#34; data-lang=&#34;en&#34;&gt;&lt;p lang=&#34;en&#34; dir=&#34;ltr&#34;&gt;Hereâ€™s a list of funding schemes and opportunities for postdoctoral fellowships curated/edited by myself and &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/khanaziz84?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;@khanaziz84&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://t.co/rq3mgsUDPp&#34;&gt;https://t.co/rq3mgsUDPp&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/hashtag/eLifeAmbassadors?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;#eLifeAmbassadors&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/eLifeCommunity?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;@eLifeCommunity&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/eLife?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;@eLife&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;mdash; Juan Quintana, PhD. (@Jquintanalcala) &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/Jquintanalcala/status/959144479356747777?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;February 1, 2018&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;blockquote class=&#34;twitter-tweet&#34; data-cards=&#34;hidden&#34; data-lang=&#34;en&#34;&gt;&lt;p lang=&#34;en&#34; dir=&#34;ltr&#34;&gt;This is an awesome catalogue of postdoc funding opportunities: &amp;gt;230 grant schemes worldwide w/ links, duration, eligibility (h/t &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/DieterLukas?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;@DieterLukas&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/Jquintanalcala?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;@Jquintanalcala&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/khanaziz84?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;@khanaziz84&lt;/a&gt;) &lt;a href=&#34;https://t.co/z2stFr5IHW&#34;&gt;https://t.co/z2stFr5IHW&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;mdash; Mike Inouye (@minouye271) &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/minouye271/status/960056071187410944?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;February 4, 2018&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;blockquote class=&#34;twitter-tweet&#34; data-cards=&#34;hidden&#34; data-lang=&#34;en&#34;&gt;&lt;p lang=&#34;en&#34; dir=&#34;ltr&#34;&gt;Post-doc and PhD friends! &lt;br&gt;Here is a very useful list of 244 different funding opportunities worldwide &lt;a href=&#34;https://t.co/wsIXlYEhZE&#34;&gt;https://t.co/wsIXlYEhZE&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;mdash; Hannah Whitby (@CopperChemist) &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/CopperChemist/status/977101690888491008?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;March 23, 2018&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://asntech.github.io/postdoc-funding-schemes/travel-grants.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;
Then the Ambassadors Lotte de Winde et al. created a detailed list of travel funding opportunities for postdocs, which is now available &lt;a href=&#34;https://asntech.github.io/postdoc-funding-schemes/travel-grants/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote class=&#34;twitter-tweet&#34; data-cards=&#34;hidden&#34; data-lang=&#34;en&#34;&gt;&lt;p lang=&#34;en&#34; dir=&#34;ltr&#34;&gt;I made a list with travel funding opportunities for postdocs: &lt;a href=&#34;https://t.co/mwTiqMqv8C&#34;&gt;https://t.co/mwTiqMqv8C&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;List is not complete yet - which ones are missing?&lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/hashtag/postdoc?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;#postdoc&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/hashtag/funding?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;#funding&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/hashtag/eLifeAmbassadors?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;#eLifeAmbassadors&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;mdash; Lotte de Winde (@lotte_dewinde) &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/lotte_dewinde/status/970599315231166464?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;March 5, 2018&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;twitter-tweet&#34; data-cards=&#34;hidden&#34; data-lang=&#34;en&#34;&gt;&lt;p lang=&#34;en&#34; dir=&#34;ltr&#34;&gt;Here&amp;#39;s a great list of &amp;gt;60 travel grant opportunities for postdocs and ECRs &lt;a href=&#34;https://t.co/KvTNfhqSSd&#34;&gt;https://t.co/KvTNfhqSSd&lt;/a&gt; curated by &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/hashtag/eLifeAmbassadors?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;#eLifeAmbassadors&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/lotte_dewinde?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;@lotte_dewinde&lt;/a&gt; et al. &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/hashtag/funding?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;#funding&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;mdash; Aziz Khan (@khanaziz84) &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/khanaziz84/status/970894803541151744?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&#34;&gt;March 6, 2018&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;script async src=&#34;https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js&#34; charset=&#34;utf-8&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We encourage the community to help to add new funding opportunities to the list by using the submit tab in the links. You can also &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/asntech/postdoc-funding-schemes&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;fork&lt;/a&gt; GitHub repo and submit a pull request.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now this funding list became ECRcentral &lt;a href=&#34;https://ecrcentral.org/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;ecrcentral.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
